From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Paul Ngo <inthewaver@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 2026 22:01:48 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] upstream: Fix gl_clear_broken workaround when transform
 feedback is active

The gl_clear_broken workaround uses glUseProgram, but this yields an
unhandled error when transform feedback is active. A crash can be
triggered by visiting, e.g.
https://registry.khronos.org/webgl/sdk/tests/deqp/functional/gles3/shaderpackingfunction.html?webglVersion=2&quiet=0&quick=1
on a device that has the gl_clear_broken workaround active.

Fix this by pausing transform feedback before the glUseProgram call, and
then resume it after the original program and buffers have been
restored. glClear isn't a part of the Vertex Processing steps, so
pausing transform feedback should be appropriate.

Bug: 492102368
Test: tools/autotest.py -C out/Default/ ES3ClearBufferTest; gl_tests;
gl_unittests; gpu_unittests; opening the linked page
Change-Id: I8bae268895186a8943c74ca7f84df23655ee9e4d
